post_text: Our thoughts are with the Ardmore Tigers at this time. We hope you are all back on the field and playing soon.
shared_text:
Ardmore City Schools
September 9 at 8:12 PM ·

We have been working with the county health department and the state epidemiologist from the Oklahoma State Department of Health to make recommendations of quarantine after we were notified of a COVID-19 positive case involving the high school football team. After investigating and consulting with the epidemiologist, it was determined that the team and associated personnel will be quarantined for 14 days, with an ending date of September 19, 2020. We continue to work with the health department on mitigation strategies to keep our students and the community safe.
text:
Our thoughts are with the Ardmore Tigers at this time. We hope you are all back on the field and playing soon.

shared_text:
Dara Campbell shared a post to the group: Shawnee Oklahoma FFA.
August 18 at 2:45 AM ·

American Farmers & Ranchers Youth Program
August 18 at 12:00 AM ·

Our next state scholarship winner we would like to recognize is Keegan Carrera! Carrera's agents are Randy and Suzanne Gilbert. Carrera served on the AFR Youth Advisory Council, volunteered at the Gold Star Classic, attended AFR Youth Leadership Summit and participated in the AFR Speech Contest and AFR Ag Achievement Contest. After graduation, Carrera plans to attend veterinary school to specialize is reproductive medicine with hopes of opening a reproductive facility in central Oklahoma.

"Through all that AFR has to offer, I have grown in my personal leadership abilities, gained self-confidence and devloped my passion for the people of Oklahoma agriculture," Carrera said. "But above all else, AFR has provided me with a second family,"

shared_text:
NASA OKSG STEM Engagement Center
July 2 at 3:00 PM ·

The NASA OKSG STEM Engagement Center had the honor and privilege of working with Denise Williams, a Shawne Public Schools educator, and her summer school students via a virtual Zoom meeting on June 9th, 2020. Over the course of 30 minutes, students engineered space suits for their Spudnauts, tested their designs, and learned about the layers of NASA's Extravehicular Mobility Unit (EMU, a space suit designed for EVA's or Extravehicular Activity). The future looks very bright with these up and coming space suit engineers!

Got the call from a freshly retired 1st grade teacher out of Jefferson Elementary in Shawnee, OK, Linda White about some help with her yard!! Oklahoma State Department of Education
June 22 at 7:00 PM ·

While this year's ceremony was cancelled due to COVID-19, we wanted to take a moment to celebrate the students and educators who earned a 2020 State Superintendent's Award for Arts Excellence!

This prestigious recognition is awarded to high school juniors and seniors who have achieved artistic and academic excellence, as well as fine arts educators and school administrators who support quality arts education in their school or district.

Join us in celebrating this year's recipients!

Congratulations to:

*Student winners: https://bit.ly/SuptArtWinners2020
*Clint Reed, Frederick High School, Frederick Public Schools - Visual art educator
*Marie Howard, Capitol Hill High School, Oklahoma City Public Schools - Assistant Principal
*Dr. April Grace, Shawnee Public Schools - Superintendent

The Shawnee News-Star
June 17 at 4:03 PM ·

ONE MORE DAY! The Best of News-Star Preps virtual awards is 6 p.m. June 18.
The Shawnee News-Star's On-Demand Preps Awards shows will be featured at the top of the event website, www.news-star.com/preps starting at 6 p.m. on Thursday, June 18.
The show can be watched there on desktop, tablet, mobile or other internet-ready devices with a web browser. Devices can be connected to TVs using HDMI connections or other video "casting" features available on the device used.
Awards will be announced as area high school students are named for Player of the Year in many sports, along with awards including Male and Female Athletes of the Year, Coach of the Year, the Courage Award and we'll recognize Athletes of the Week. This area's 16 Students of the Month will be honored and we'll announce the overall Student of the Year, who will win a new Jeep Renegade from Patriot Auto Group!

post_text:
ATTENTION PARENTS:

If your student is or was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income. The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020 deadline at https://secure.okcollegestart.org/applications/Oklahoma_Promise/apply.html?application_id=3544.

You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received.

Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu.

Our SHS Seniors will have a senior parade on May 18th!

The Seniors will meet at 2 p.m. on the west side of Dillard’s in the Shawnee Mall parking lot. Their parade will begin at 2:30 pm. at the mall and end at Shawnee High School. They will have a police escort.

Friends and family, please line up along Kickapoo to show support! Let's cheer for the #SHSCLASSOF2020! #ShawneeSTRONG

It’s time to fill out your 2020 Census! Here’s how:

Go to the website: my2020Census.gov.
Click on the button that says “Start Questionnaire”
Don’t have access to the internet or a smart phone or need assistance in another language? Call (844) 330-2020. It’s easy and safe.
No Census ID? No problem! Everyone can fill out the Census right now.

If you don’t have a Census ID, you can choose “If you do not have a Census ID, click here.” It will ask you to fill out some basic information, like your address, and then you can get started!

Fill out your 2020 Census today at my2020census.gov. When everyone counts, everyone wins!
text:
It’s time to fill out your 2020 Census! Here’s how:

Go to the website: my2020Census.gov.
Click on the button that says “Start Questionnaire”
Don’t have access to the internet or a smart phone or need assistance in another language? Call (844) 330-2020. It’s easy and safe.
No Census ID? No problem! Everyone can fill out the Census right now.

If you don’t have a Census ID, you can choose “If you do not have a Census ID, click here.” It will ask you to fill out some basic information, like your address, and then you can get started!

Fill out your 2020 Census today at my2020census.gov. When everyone counts, everyone wins!

“[Shawnee Public Schools is] very supportive of Early Childhood. The whole state is but especially Shawnee district. They want the very best for these kids because they realize that if we can meet these children’s needs then as they grow they’re going to continue to do well in education and then later as a citizen,” Ann Butler Worden said.

Mrs. Worden, you are a wonderful administrator who will be missed. Congratulations on your upcoming retirement.

post_text: Jim Thorpe Academy and Shawnee High School graduates Winter Wolfe and Kendall Powell, representing a new program from TThe Chickasaw Nation were guest speakers in Jim Thorpe Academy's Native American Studies class recently. The Chickasaw Nation created the program to raise awareness for the plight of Missing-Murdered-Indigenous-Women/People. The duo are also former students of Mr. Rolette's Native American Studies Class. They indicated to current students that they believed that the skills and confidence that they were taught at the Academy were very instrumental in preparing them for their current positions and for their futures. Pictured are, from left, Wolfe, Rolette, and Powell.

shared_text:
Shawnee Wrestling
February 22 at 8:10 PM ·

Just like that the wolves have the ROUND OF THE TOURNAMENT!! On the strength of 2 falls, a 13-2 major decision, a 6-0 decision, and a 4-3 nail biter in the consolation semi-final blood round, WE HAVE 6 GOING TO THE STATE TOURNAMENT!!!! Could not be more proud of the boys in blue!! It’s been a heck of a season with a lot of ups and downs, but we believed and stayed the course and it’s all paying off at the perfect time!

Jordan Lomeli will wrestle for 1st while Angelo Reyes, Spencer Rochelle, Sam Anderson, Kyle Helie, and Lane Williams all wrestle for 3rd place today at 4:00 pm!! Come out and support your STATE QUALIFIED SHAWNEE WOLVES WRESTLERS!!!

#ShawneeSTRONG #ShawneeWRESTLIN #BLUEANDWHITEFIGHT

post_text:
Congratulations to SHS HOWL (Honoring Outstanding Wolf Leadership) Award recipient Dr. Brett Scott. Mary Rolette presented Dr. Scott with the HOWL Award and had this to say about her co-worker:

"Dr. Scott possesses a 24/7 on-the-clock dedication. Shawnee FFA gives back to the community and represents Shawnee High School favorably. They go to SECC and read to the students. They have a Saturday toy drive in December and donate those toys to The Salvation Army. In prior years, they have made quilts and presented the quilts to nursing home residents. They participate at fairs, shows, and competitions. He helps the students earn scholarships and provides them with a true role model as an Ag teacher, advisor, and good person. They received National recognition for the first time! He also was the main organizer of SHS CareerTech's career fair last year with over 600 students participating and 20 vendors."

Congratulations, Dr. Scott! Thank you for representing SHS and demonstrating service, respect, nobility, and generosity. #ShawneeSTRONG

shared_text:
Shawnee Wrestling
December 22, 2019 at 1:06 AM ·

We battled hard today! Brought 11 and placed 7 in the top 4! Placers went as follows: Jordan Lomeli CHAMPION 132lbs (5 falls 7:53), Jose Cervantes CHAMPION 138lbs (4 falls 6:59), Christien Taylor 2nd place 113 lbs, Brenner James 2nd place 120 lbs, Kyle Helie 2nd place 182 lbs, Spencer Rochelle 3rd place 145 lbs, & Sam Anderson 3rd place 170 lbs. Angelo Reyes and Logan Cash both finished 5th place respectively. We brought home some individual hardware, but missed out on 2nd place and a team award by 8 points. All good, we wouldn’t have been satisfied with 2nd place anyway!! We are headed in the right direction! Now for a well earned rest to recover and get ready to kick it into high gear and come into 2020 with a clear vision of the mission!! Happy Holidays from your Wolfpack Wrestling team!! Hope everyone has a great one! 🐺💙🤼‍♂️🎄#ShawneeSTRONG #WolfpackWrestlin

Shawnee Wrestling
December 12, 2019 at 2:36 PM ·

💓 Feel good story! Lone senior and team captain Jose Cervantes poses with his Christmas gifts for Christmas Connection! Christmas Connection is a gift exchange program for kids who are more financially challenged so that they may have a Happy Holiday even if life is weighing hard on their families! He took great pride and time in gathering his gifts for the kids and made sure to get them things they would really enjoy and get great use out of! Instead of paying back the kindness he has received Jose is instead paying it forward! So fortunate to have this kind of leadership and example for our program! First picture is Jose today, 2nd picture is Jose at 4 years old!ShawneeSTRONG #Elevate #payitforward

Shawnee Wrestling
December 6, 2019 at 1:42 PM ·

So we ended up losing to mustang 64-15. We won’t make any excuses!! Hats off to those dudes, they are tough! Glad they could come out and we got a chance to see what some of the guys who have stood at the top look like! The score is not a good indicator of the Dual and you should be proud of these guys for representing the Shawnee Community well!! We just want to take this time to thank the fans that came and supported us! That place was rocking for a while. We rallied off 3 wins in a row and 2 were via fall! There were bright spots, and we have things to build on! You win or you learn, and we learned a lot last night! Until next time 🐺💪#ShawneeSTRONG #noexcuses #betternexttime

Congratulations to our Shawnee Public Schools Support Employee and "New to the Pack" Employee for November, Nancy Johnson and Nik Turner, respectively.

Nancy has been a Shawnee bus driver since 2005. She absolutely loves her students and is determined to see them succeed at Jim Thorpe Academy. Nancy is known for going the extra mile and will always look for ways to lend a helping hand. Nancy, you are definitely #ShawneeSTRONG

Nik Turner is a social studies teacher at Shawnee Middle School and the varsity wrestling coach for Shawnee High School. Coach Turner has shown his students what service learning is and the positive change it can bring to others. He shows what giving back and generosity can accomplish when drilled into a team environment. We are proud Coach Turner is part of the #ShawneeSTRONG community.

post_text: Will Rogers 1st graders have studied the art of making fry bread in Native American cultures this week. Librarian Chandra Swisher read the book “Fry Bread: A Native American Family Story” to students, & Native American Advisor Serena Neely made fry bread for students to taste. Ms. Neely also showed students how to make their own fry bread. Some students found their Native American nations in the end pages of the picture book written by Seminole Nation citizen Kevin Noble Maillard, a former Oklahoma resident who now writes and teaches law in New York.

Thank you to our #communitypartners with @community_renewal and @shawneeforward for being our heroes. #WeCare #worldkindnessday #ShawneeSTRONG

post_text:
Congratulations to SHS HOWL Award recipient Jana Sturgell. Coach Branson presented Mrs. Sturgell with the HOWL Award and had this to say about her co-worker, "Mrs. Sturgell started our first annual philanthropy week (HOWL Week) to promote people uniting for a good cause. She worked really hard and successfully brought the school and community together to help some of our students go to the Special Olympics."

Congratulations, Mrs Sturgell! Thank you for representing SHS and demonstrating service, respect and generosity. #ShawneeSTRONG

Shawnee Middle School
November 8, 2019 at 11:19 PM ·

For the second year in a row we have received handmade scarves and hats for our students from the local group, Down Home Friends. The ladies group crocheted and sewed each item over the last couple of months. We now have 80 scarves, 69 hats, 17 headbands, and 40 pairs of socks. These are for any SMS student who might need a little extra warmth this winter. Thank you! 🐺❤️🧣

post_text: Will Rogers Art Show Award winners Karlee Fuller, 3rd place (third from left); Madilynn Carter, 2nd place; and Booker Dahlman, 1st place; were recognized by Kyle Rosebure of BancFirst Insurance Services (right). Also congratulating the winners are (from left) Trevor Mastin, art teacher, and Dr. April Grace, superintendent. Serving as judge for the Will Rogers Art Show was Amber DuBoise-Shepherd from Mabee-Gerrer Museum of Art (not pictured).
text: Will Rogers Art Show Award winners Karlee Fuller, 3rd place (third from left); Madilynn Carter, 2nd place; and Booker Dahlman, 1st place; were recognized by Kyle Rosebure of BancFirst Insurance Services (right). Also congratulating the winners are (from left) Trevor Mastin, art teacher, and Dr. April Grace, superintendent.
